<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1909-12-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1909-12-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="44" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d44">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 3382/25A.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Belgian
                                Minister</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-12-22"><hi rend="italic">December 22,
                                    1909</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Minister</hi>: The President desires me
                            to say that he will attend the services to be held at St. Matthew’s
                            Church tomorrow morning, at half past 10 o’clock, in memory of His late
                            Majesty King Leopold.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington
                            Wilson.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>